section.section:
A person may not set a haul seine exceeding 50 feet in length in the following waters:
Herring Bay from a line drawn from the extreme projection of Parker's Island Point into the Chesapeake Bay to the extreme point of Holland Point;
South River, Rhode River, and West River;
From a line drawn from the extreme projection from Thomas Point into the Chesapeake Bay to the extreme point of Curtis Point;
Within the headlands of Whitehall Creek; and
Within the headlands of Meridith Creek and Lake Ogleton.
